news.title: Institutional investments in real estate to cross $10 billion in 2025: JLL
news.para: Indian real estate is set for record institutional investment in 2025, projected to exceed $10 billion. This marks a significant increase, driven by domestic capital and sustained foreign interest. The office sector is leading the charge, with Bengaluru and Mumbai Metropolitan Region as top destinations.

news.title: Net office leasing hits 55 million sq ft in 2025 across top cities: Anarock
news.para: In 2025, Indian office leasing set a new benchmark, totaling 55.16 million sq ft, marking a robust 10% increase. Bengaluru continued to lead the chart, although it saw a minor decline. In contrast, Pune experienced an astonishing 63% growth, fueled by a surge in demand from global capability centers, which accounted for 41% of the total.

news.title: Guntur civic body adopts resolution to merge 18 villages ahead of boundary freeze deadline
news.para: Guntur Municipal Corporation hastily passed a resolution to merge 18 villages ahead of a central deadline, adding seven villages due to legislative pressure. While aiming for million-plus city status, the process faces delays due to upcoming elections and the need for fresh approvals, raising concerns about political maneuvering.

news.title: Property registrations dip as land prices rise & private layouts proliferate in Haveri
news.para: Property registrations in Haveri district have plummeted due to soaring land prices and a surge in private layouts.  Monthly registrations have fallen significantly, indicating buyer hesitation amidst escalating costs and limited affordable options.  Despite government reforms, steep price hikes are deterring ordinary buyers, leading to a slump in the real estate market and reduced government revenue.

news.title: Additional registrar can cancel sale deed for illegal cooperative society allotment: Karnataka HC
news.para: Karnataka High Court ruled that the additional registrar of cooperative societies can cancel registered sale deeds if based on illegal allotments. Justice Suraj Govindaraj clarified that while due process and hearing the affected party are crucial, the registrar has the power to intervene in such cases, impacting numerous cooperative housing disputes.

news.title: NGT rejects appeal to revoke cancellation of EC for sand mining on Dhasan in Jhansi
news.para: The National Green Tribunal has rejected an appeal to reinstate environmental clearance for sand mining on the Dhasan river in Jhansi. The clearance was previously cancelled by UP SEIAA due to gross irregularities and environmental threats. The NGT cited the appeal being filed beyond the 90-day limitation period as the reason for dismissal.

news.title: Lucknow civic body to implement new system for house tax assessment
news.para: The Lucknow Municipal Corporation is implementing a Property Tax Management System (PTMS) to enhance transparency in house tax assessments and curb discrepancies. This digital system will create a building-wise database, enabling authorities to compare actual construction with recorded data, identify under-assessed properties, and improve accountability in tax calculations.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: NMMC issues notices to CIDCO for pollution control norm violations at two housing project sites
news.para: The Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation has sent formal warnings to CIDCO regarding significant breaches of pollution guidelines at two of its housing projects. The NMMC is insisting that CIDCO take immediate steps to address these issues and submit a comprehensive report detailing the actions taken to rectify the situation.

news.title: Delhi Police bust ₹12 crore luxury property fraud, arrest five in Gurugram
news.para: Delhi Police have made headlines after arresting five individuals involved in an elaborate property fraud scheme. The thieves are accused of defrauding a man of Rs 12 crore through the sale of a fictitious luxury property, underpinned by forged documents. Authorities suspect this syndicate has swindled unsuspecting victims nationwide, racking up over Rs 200 crore in fraudulent activities.

news.title: Technopark’s QUAD project construction to begin in January 2026
news.para: Construction on Technopark's QUAD project, Kerala's largest integrated IT township, is set to commence next month. Technopark is inviting private co-developers to partner in building additional premium IT and commercial assets within the campus. This initiative aims to create a self-sustained ecosystem, generating thousands of jobs and boosting Thiruvananthapuram's tech hub status.

news.title: I-T department attaches 282 acres near Hyderabad in ₹2,000 crore benami land case
news.para: Hyderabad's Income Tax Department has provisionally attached 282 acres worth ₹2,002 crore, suspecting benami transactions. Former Sanghi Industries promoters Ravi Sanghi and family are accused of undervaluing land sales to bypass SEBI norms and defraud minority shareholders. The investigation points to a conspiracy to siphon corporate assets.

news.title: Ambuja Neotia Group to revive stalled Usshar Project at Batanagar, Kolkata
news.para: Ambuja Housing & Urban Infrastructure Company has secured National Company Law Tribunal approval. The company will take over the Usshar Project at Batanagar. The company will pay ₹34 crore upfront, complete and hand over residences to Usshar home buyers.

news.title: MahaRERA recovery sluggish in state, only 33% of ₹792 crore dues collected
news.para: Recovery of funds for homebuyers through MahaRERA warrants is significantly slow, with only a third of the Rs 791.55 crore due having been collected. Despite numerous complaints and favorable orders, homebuyers are experiencing prolonged delays in receiving their money, highlighting systemic enforcement issues.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks Splendor Buildwell to clear dues of investors in 90 days
news.para: Haryana RERA has ordered Splendor Buildwell to pay over Rs 71.5 per sq ft monthly assured returns to investors Tripti and Amit Vohra for their commercial units in Spectrum One. The developer must also formalize property titles within 90 days, with pending dues to be released with interest.

news.title: Delhi: Cafe at Baansera among 150 plots and sites to be e-auctioned to boost DDA’s revenue
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is set to e-auction over 150 vacant sites and plots next month, including residential, commercial, and industrial properties. Registrations open on December 30 for these assets, aiming to boost revenue.

news.title: Union minister inaugurates tenements constructed under smart city mission
news.para: Union Minister Nityanand Rai took significant steps towards community welfare by inaugurating affordable housing for sanitary workers in Chinnayapuram. He also unveiled a Rs 17 crore mini stadium at Anna Thidal, which will serve as a vibrant hub for youth and locals to engage in sports and recreation.

news.title: Housing sales fall 14% in 2025 across top cities, but value rises 6%: Anarock
news.para: The year 2025 marked a pivotal change for housing sales in major Indian metros, witnessing a 14% drop in the number of transactions. Interestingly, the total value of sold properties climbed by 6%, underscoring a flourishing demand for upscale real estate. Meanwhile, the supply of new housing remained steady with a spike in luxury launches.

news.title: Odisha: Education minister distributes PMAY-U work orders in Sambalpur
news.para: Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan distributed work orders for 855 houses under PMAY (Urban) in Sambalpur, a significant step for inclusive urban development. Beneficiaries also received aid under the Madhu Babu Pension Yojana at a program attended by state ministers and local officials.

news.title: Jaipur: Illegal constructions removed from Hawa Mahal-Amber zone
news.para: The Jaipur Municipal Corporation (JMC) conducted a demolition drive against illegal constructions on government land in the Hawa Mahal-Amber zone. Nearly 4 bighas of JMC land were cleared in Kalalon Ki Dhani after demarcation confirmed encroachment. Further unauthorized constructions were also removed in Chandrashekhar Azad Colony.

news.title: Noida Metro Rail Corporation offers commercial space at three metro stations
news.para: Noida Metro Rail Corporation is leasing commercial spaces at Sector 81, Sector 83, and Depot metro stations on the Aqua Line to boost non-fare box revenue. Applications are due by January 5, 2026, with a 15-year license period. This initiative supports NMRC's financial strategy as ridership stands at 68,869 daily passengers.
